        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('CardDAV'); ?>
        <p><strong>vCard Extensions to WebDAV (CardDAV)</strong> is an address book client / server protocol designed to allow users to access and share contact data on a server.</p>
        <p>The CardDAV protocol was developed by the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('IETF', 'C'); ?> and has been published as <?php echo $this->stencil->addRFCLink('6352'); ?> in August 2011. CardDAV is based on <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('WebDAV', 'WD'); ?>, which is based on <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('HTTP', 'IPA'); ?>, and it uses <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('vCard', 'WD'); ?> for contact data.<p></p>
